# 2. Protection Checks

## Linux

```bash
checksec chall
```

Look for:

```text
Canary
NX
PIE
RELRO
```

Mostly useful in pwn/rev hybrids.

---

# 3. String Hunting

90% of beginner rev challenges die here.

```bash
strings chall
```

Better:

```bash
strings -n 5 chall
```

Search:

```bash
strings chall | grep flag
strings chall | grep CTF
strings chall | grep password
```

---

# 4. Detect Packing

## UPX

```bash
strings chall | grep UPX
```

or

```bash
upx -t chall
```

Unpack:

```bash
upx -d chall
```

---

## Packed PE

Use:

```text
PEStudio
Detect It Easy (DIE)
```

---

# 5. Static Analysis

## Open in Ghidra

Find:

```text
main()
WinMain()
entry()
```

---

## Rename Variables

Bad:

```c
local_10
local_20
```

Good:

```c
user_input
flag
key
```

Renaming makes life easier.

